KeNHA  scored highest at 81 per cent for maintaining 13,344km of the targeted 16,580km of its road networks using the KRB fund distributes.The KeNHA was allocated the highest at Sh23.6 billion from the fund due to its lengthy networks of roads under its watch. The Kenya Rural Roads Authority (KeRRA) was ranked poorest among the road agencies in the utilisation of the funds milked from motorists for road maintenance.
The Kenya Roads Board reports on the use of the fund motorists contribute to help keep roads in good condition shows that the rural roads agency had only achieved 28 per cent of the planned maintained works for the period to June 2020.



